title: what makes spiderverse different
body:
peter b. parker the peter parker that we spend the most time with is older, weathered, depressed, we’ve never had a middle-aged peter onscreen before, even in the comics he’s perpetually young and, for lack of a better word, fresh, bright and full of energy, peter b. almost resents being spiderman. he’s tired. he’s not a peter parker we’re used to, but many can still relate to, older fans who are middle-aged themselves, parents, most millennials/older gen z

miles morales is not black peter parker within his neighbourhood, in that first long take, we see that he’s popular, he has friends, he’s an artist, he has both of his parents, he has three father figures, he has people guiding him in being a spider-person, everything peter parker wasn’t and didn’t have. spiderverse is his origin story.

all of this leads onto what truly makes the story of spiderverse different to the spiderman origin stories, the message 

spiderman and spidermen stories are generally a metaphor for puberty, the whole changing body, new experiences blah blah blah, but spiderman into the spiderverse isn’t, hell, miles specifically denies that he’s going through puberty, no, the main message of spiderverse, is you are not alone. 

this could probably be extended to a metaphor for being queer and the lgbt community. 

miles wants to deny that he’s anything like spiderman at the beginning, he feels as though everyone’s looking at him and singling him out and talking about him. he finds his powers a hindrance, unwanted, he doesn’t want to be spiderman. but he finds a group of people just like him, peter b. shows him how to be spiderman and he takes that identity, of spiderman, by the end

summary: Played around with this the last few days... it might end up in a future story, so here’s a little peak at something, odd but...
body:
Played around with this the last few days… it might end up in a future story, so here’s a little peak at something, odd but fun 

Also, a little thanks to @dystopian-dez382 and @cyenakarma for letting me bounce this idea off you both.

Peter, sitting on the top of the couch, asks Rhodey, “So, what’s your favorite part of being a super hero?”

Venom/Eddie walk in, without thinking, Venom says, “Pile of bodies, pile of heads.”

Rhodey shakes his head and sighs.

From the kitchen, Wade is heard singing, “These are a few of my favorite things!”

body:
Flirting in the Lab - greengreed - The Spectacular Spider-Man (Cartoon) [Archive of Our Own]

Oh look… A new fic 👀 based on TSSM. Also the glasses thing was based on a comic, sidney one comic, Norman snatches Otto’s glasses… And it’s kinda cute but then it becomes not cute. These bois are so complicated. Anyway, give it a read if you’d like! ❤️✨

I might make more TSSM fics because I hardcore ship Otto and Norman there, even if they clearly very much dislike each other. I like shy Otto. Such a cutie 💕 I kinda wanna write a PS4 game fic… Anyway yeah!

If you have requests for a fic, I will literally write whatever (Spider-Man/Marvel related) in the next few coming days. If you have a Norman x Otto (especially if it has the goblin) plot point, even better! Since they’re my OTP. Anyway… yeah! That’s all! Thanks for reading, if you did! 💚

summary: i have so many thoughts clint. i’m pretty sure everything is afraid of fire. what experience led you to this horse-specific...
caption:
i have so many thoughts

  1. clint. i’m pretty sure everything is afraid of fire.
  2. what experience led you to this horse-specific conclusion
  3. if the horse was spooked by a skateboard, why would seeing an arrow explode in front of it make it go “oh maybe i should chill out and not run full equine throttle in another direction”
  4. and yet it worked.
  5. clint immediately moves past “horse fire” because the skateboarder pushed him down earlier and he wants sweet petty vengeance

Peter: oh yeah, cool. i’ll grab one in a little bit
Tony: they’re warm. big...
body:
Tony: hey, kid. i made pancakes, do you want one?

Peter: oh yeah, cool. i’ll grab one in a little bit

Tony: they’re warm. big too.

Peter: soon

Tony: want me to bring one through for you?

Peter: no, i’m ok

Tony: ok

*five minutes pass*

Tony, coming through with pancake in his bare hand, no plate: brought u a pancake. feel how warm.

Peter, poking and gently accepting the warm pancake: oh… okay thanks

Peter, poking and gently accepting the warm pancake: oh… okay thanks
